[09:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ultra plan, so I might as well use it, is just upload the video back to Gemini and say like, "Hey, this is weird jump cut. Uh, can you give me a prompt that fixes that?" &gt;&gt; The bunker is our only chance. &gt;&gt; A chance to what? To be the last ones'

[09:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'left. &gt;&gt; And it did indeed fix that cut. Now, granted, it did not give us another cut. Instead, it gave us a push in. and also put a weird like howling wolf in the background who is clearly going to eat everyone in the bunker by the end of'

[09:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this movie. But I did want to highlight that is a way to work with an LLM when you\'re not getting a desired output. You know, just ask. Now, I do want to point out that JSON prompting can sometimes get frustrating, especially when you\'re trying to diagnose a problem. Uh, take'

[10:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for example our, you know, hard-nosed nor detective here. Uh, running this with a natural language prompt to get a twofer out of it. We end up with this. It was a Tuesday when she walked in. Nothing good ever happens on a Tuesday.'

[10:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Overall, a pretty solid output. I am a little concerned about our guy\'s liver considering that he\'s on his third glass now. And we can tell by the lighting. The sun hasn\'t even gone down yet. Um, yeah, our guy is putting the hard and'

[10:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'hard boiled. Now, the problem with our JSON output of the same prompt was, well, I\'ll I\'ll let you check it out. &gt;&gt; It was a Tuesday when she walked in. Nothing good ever happens on a Tuesday.'

[10:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; I mean, is crime noir, country, musical a thing? Uh, I apparently I guess we just made it and I got to say it was a bit of a hassle to figure out. Gemini actually couldn\'t figure it out. Uh, it'

[11:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'turns out that it was something between the voice over uh the grally and tired and then the background melody playing continuously. Something about those combinations for some reason triggers country music. Now, one additional benefit, uh, kind of a hack that you can'

[11:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'utilize with JSON prompting is something that I\'ve documented a few times on the channel. If you use an image prompt, you can use a prompt like immediately cut to a completely different situation. And a'

[11:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lot of times the attributes of that image will then carry over. Now, this does not work all the time, and a lot of times, especially with characters, you\'ll just have a character kind of hanging out in that initial environment. That said, with JSON prompting, we can'

[11:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'take an image like this and immediately have her move over into like a cyberpunk setting. [Music] Where can I find the dark wizard? &gt;&gt; Or for some strange reason, she\'s picked'

[11:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'up a gig as an office temp. &gt;&gt; Where can I find the dark wizard? &gt;&gt; I love the fact that Bill from accounting here is like, I got to talk'

[12:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to HR about this lady. But yeah, by utilizing a JSON prompt of something like scene description, then timing it at zero to zero seconds um and then just completely changing the prompt, you do seem to have a very high success rate. So ultimately, when it comes down to'

[12:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'natural language prompting or JSON prompting, you know, I I honestly I don\'t think that there\'s a clear winner either way. As I always say, there is no right or wrong way to prompt. You know, experiment around, see which one you'

